<exercise>
  <title>C4 - Homogeneous second-order linear IVP (ver. 57)</title>
  <statement>
    <p>Find the solution to the given IVP.</p>
    <me>y''+16y = 0 \hspace{1em} y(0) = 3 , y'(0) = -12</me>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>y= 3 \, \cos\left(4 \, t\right) - 3 \, \sin\left(4 \, t\right)</me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
